            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains a resolution of the citizens of Upper Alton, Illinois, proposed by Robert Smith on January 30, 1836, concerning the location of the Cumberland Road, and a letter of August 18, 1842, from Smith to Alexander M. K. Dubois, clerk of the circuit court of Macoupin County, regarding the payment of a mortgage on land in that county.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


